      <TYPE> FUNCTION VAL_SQRT<T>( BAD, ARG, STATUS )
*+
*  Name:
*     VAL_SQRT<T>

*  Purpose:
*     Evaluate the <COMM> square root function.

*  Language:
*     Starlink Fortran

*  Invocation:
*     RESULT = VAL_SQRT<T>( BAD, ARG, STATUS )

*  Description:
*     The routine evaluates the square root function for a single
*     argument of type <COMM>.  If a numerical error occurs, the value
*     VAL__BAD<T> is returned and a STATUS value is set.

*  Arguments:
*     BAD = LOGICAL (Given)
*        Whether the argument value (ARG) may be "bad".
*     ARG = <TYPE> (Given)
*        The <COMM> argument of the square root function.
*     STATUS = INTEGER (Given & Returned)
*        This should be set to SAI__OK on entry, otherwise the routine
*        returns immediately with the result VAL__BAD<T>.  A STATUS
*        value will be set by this routine if a numerical error occurs.

*  Returned Value:
*     VAL_SQRT<T> = <TYPE>
*        Returns the evaluated square root function result as a <COMM>
*        value.  The value VAL__BAD<T> will be returned under error
*        conditions.

